{"id": "EUVD-2022-55396", "enisaUuid": "c782906e-4124-3f3e-8013-98b9d21e44ff", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nstaging: fbtft: core: set smem_len before fb_deferred_io_init call\n\nThe fbtft_framebuffer_alloc() calls fb_deferred_io_init() before\ninitializing info->fix.smem_len.  It is set to zero by the\nframebuffer_alloc() function.  It will trigger a WARN_ON() at the\nstart of fb_deferred_io_init() and the function will not do anything.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:49", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-18T18:32:46", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4178bfa3fc9de556dfe248a6eabe29280f0ffda5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5185c319e8ea67657e0d3edd520a7276516c506a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6ae6abe240306f878557d6eadd950a2e2561f59f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/81e878887ff82a7dd42f22951391069a5d520627", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50130"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50130"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "022c6cf3-3cf3-3e6c-ba42-37ec045d9c1c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "856082f021a28221db2c32bd0531614a8382be67 <6ae6abe240306f878557d6eadd950a2e2561f59f"}, {"id": "3f1dfe3e-d184-3d63-aecc-ca1645b41576", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.19"}, {"id": "488412c4-2fa7-3f2f-acfe-0e76acd199fc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "549aebfe-4205-3e93-a7f2-f83f7e4bd56c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.2"}, {"id": "84218280-d85e-3f07-b6ad-c1357830d75a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e79b2b2aadeffe1db54a6b569b9b621575c3eb07 <4178bfa3fc9de556dfe248a6eabe29280f0ffda5"}, {"id": "8c3e9507-4caa-3c4f-81aa-db8def850d01", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "856082f021a28221db2c32bd0531614a8382be67 <81e878887ff82a7dd42f22951391069a5d520627"}, {"id": "a6fb3cb8-a8eb-3809-b4e3-f970fc3fb424", "product": {"name": "